    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "AIR MAILA\nhis cover was carried in\na caraboa-drawn cart,\nBeetle Nut Express,\nfrom Dededo 5 miles to\nD\nAgana, the capital of Guam,\nE\nJUL\n4\n4 PM\n1937\nGUAN\nE\nand there postmarked.\nL\nThe Pan American Airway Co.\ntransported it 8 miles by truck\nv Special Delivery\nA to these\nClipper. E\nL It was flown via Wake, Midway \u0026 R\nHawaii to Alameda, California\nY\nwhere its flight continued\nvia other airmail routes.\nSPONSORS; IRETZLER \u0026 V088\nAIR MAIL.\n509\nMiss I. Marion Wood,\nOverbrook,\nNew Hartford, Conn.",
